cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SD 

This paper focuses on learning low-dimensional representations of text-annotated nodes in a graph, which is a common problem in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also deals with dynamic graphs, which suggests that it could be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing).
